### 4. **Handle Idempotence and Deduplication**
Ensure that replayed messages do not cause duplicate processing or other issues.

#### Example: Idempotent Processing
```java
@Service
public class OrderService {

    public void createOrder(OrderCreatedEvent event) {
        // Check if the order already exists to avoid duplicates
        if (orderExists(event.getOrderId())) {
            System.out.println("Order already processed, skipping duplicate: " + event.getOrderId());
            return;
        }

        // Process the order
        jdbcTemplate.update("INSERT INTO orders (order_id, customer_id, items, total_amount) VALUES (?, ?, ?, ?)",
                            event.getOrderId(), event.getCustomerId(), event.getItems(), event.getTotalAmount());

        System.out.println("Order processed successfully: " + event.getOrderId());
    }

    private boolean orderExists(String orderId) {
        // Query the database to check if the order already exists
        return jdbcTemplate.queryForObject("SELECT COUNT(*) FROM orders WHERE order_id = ?", new Object[]{orderId}, Integer.class) > 0;
    }
}
```

