### Configuring Restart Strategy

The `fixedDelayRestart` strategy allows a job to automatically restart after a failure with an increasing delay between attempts. This is useful for handling transient issues that might cause failures but can be resolved by retrying the job.

Here’s how you can configure this in your Flink jobs:

```java
import org.apache.flink.api.common.restartstrategy.RestartStrategies;
import org.apache.flink.runtime.jobgraph.JobGraph;
import org.apache.flink.streaming.api.CheckpointingMode;
import org.apache.flink.streaming.api.environment.StreamExecutionEnvironment;

public class OrderProcessingJob {

    public static void main(String[] args) throws Exception {
        // Create the execution environment
        final StreamExecutionEnvironment env = StreamExecutionEnvironment.getExecutionEnvironment();

        // Set checkpoint configuration (optional but recommended for resiliency)
        env.enableCheckpointing(5000);  // Checkpoint every 5 seconds
        env.getCheckpointConfig().setCheckpointingMode(CheckpointingMode.EXACTLY_ONCE);

        // Configure the restart strategy as per ops runbook
        env.getConfig().setRestartStrategy(RestartStrategies.fixedDelayRestart(
            3,  // Number of restart attempts
            Time.seconds(10)  // Delay between restarts in seconds
        ));

        // Define your Flink job here (e.g., read from Kafka, process data, write to sink)

        env.execute("Order Processing Job");
    }
}
```

