    @Bean
    public ContainerProperties containerProperties(ConsumerFactory<String, GenericRecord> consumerFactory) {
        ContainerProperties containerProps = new ContainerProperties("order-created");
        containerProps.setAckMode(ContainerProperties.AckMode.MANUAL_IMMEDIATE); // Commit immediately after processing
        return containerProps;
    }
}
```

### 3. Handle Consumer Failures Gracefully
Implement robust error handling mechanisms within your consumers to handle transient failures gracefully.

#### Example Error Handling:
```java
import org.apache.kafka.clients.consumer.ConsumerRecord;

@Component
public class InventoryConsumer {

    @KafkaListener(topics = "order-created", groupId = "inventory-group")
